ISLAMABAD, June 10 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan reported 72 new COVID-19 cases during the last 24 hours, the country's ministry of health said on Friday. The tally of infected people increased to 1,531,039 after adding the new cases, according to the data released by the ministry. A total of 30,381 people died from COVID-19 in Pakistan after two more deaths were recorded on Thursday, according to the ministry's statistics. On Thursday, 15,129 tests for COVID-19 were conducted in Pakistan while the positivity rate stood at 0.48 percent. Currently, 50 patients are in critical condition in the South Asian country.  â– 